Returning to the Met Gala, Manish Malhotra (@manishmalhotra05) presented a couture moment rooted in emotion, heritage, and craft. Inspired by Mumbai, the city that shaped his creative journey, the designer reimagined the ivory bandhgala with a sculptural cape—brought to life over 960 hours by 50 artisans. Intricate dori, zardozi, chikankari, and kasab embroidery unfolded as storytelling, while the signatures of each craftsman were woven into the garment itself.
