For his second appearance at the Met Gala, Manish Malhotra (@manishmalhotra05) presents a deeply personal couture look inspired by Mumbai and the artisans at his atelier (@manishmalhotraworld). Wearing an Indian bandhgala with an architectural cape crafted over 960 hours by 50 artisans across Delhi and Mumbai, the ensemble celebrates Indian craftsmanship through dori work, zardozi, chikankari, and kasab, with subtle references to Mumbai woven throughout. Finished with signature MM collar pins from Manish Malhotra High Jewellery (@manishmalhotrajewellery).
